thinkpad_world_wallpaper_revived
================================

This project is a modern, live reimplementation of the classic IBM/ThinkPad
"World Time" Active Desktop wallpaper.

Credits & lineage
------------------
- Original concept & artwork: IBM / Lenovo ThinkPad "World Time" Active Desktop
  (design lineage attributed to David Hill's ThinkPad design team).
- Open-source HTML/JS tribute (GPL): Maxim Proskurnya, "World Time Wallpaper"
  (v2.4.x), from which the city offsets used to calibrate the map projection were
  derived. <axofiber at gmail.com>

Artwork licensing — IMPORTANT (read before publishing)
------------------------------------------------------
The raster world map under `worldtime/assets/` (`world.time.1400x1050.png`) is the
original IBM/Lenovo ThinkPad artwork and is **copyright IBM/Lenovo**. It is bundled
here for personal/local use only.

Before publishing this repository publicly, EITHER:
  (a) ship only the vector map (map_style = "vector", see below) and remove the raster
      artwork under worldtime/assets/, OR
  (b) obtain appropriate permission / rely on a defensible fair-use basis.

Vector map (Phase B) — cleanly licensed, the recommended public default
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
`map_style = "vector"` draws the world from Natural Earth data bundled under
`worldtime/geodata/` (ne_110m_land, ne_110m_admin_0_countries, ne_10m_time_zones for the
honest zig-zag timezone boundaries + GMT column, ne_10m_geographic_lines for the
International Date Line). Natural Earth is in the **public domain**
(https://www.naturalearthdata.com/about/terms-of-use/) and is freely redistributable. The
vector map is fully theme-able (blue / dark / custom) and contains no IBM/Lenovo artwork,
so it is the recommended map for any public release.

"ThinkPad" wordmark
-------------------
The optional bottom-left "ThinkPad" wordmark (config `logo = true`) is drawn as text
and is a Lenovo trademark. It is fine for personal use; set `logo = false` for any
public or redistributed build to avoid implying endorsement.

The Python code in this repository is licensed GPL-2.0-or-later (see LICENSE),
consistent with the GPL tribute it descends from.
